dialogue.speaker: Dilbert
dialogue.text: I DON'T QUITE UNDERSTAND WHAT SCIENTIFIC PRINCIPLE YOU INTEND TO DISCOVER WITH A BOWL OF SOUP AND A NECKTIE.

dialogue.speaker: Dogbert
dialogue.text: I'M TESTING THE STRANGE ATTRACTION BETWEEN STAINING LIQUIDS AND NEW TIES.

dialogue.speaker: Dogbert
dialogue.text: I WONDER HOW NEWTON MISSED THIS LITTLE GRAVITATIONAL ODDITY.
